    {
      "id": "t0HqJOyTjDYgmiTXhnfhE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 218.11483568183087,
      "y": 7126.451453779987,
      "width": 757.0607299804688,
      "height": 434.16528762516987,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3j",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1413385499,
      "version": 205,
      "versionNonce": 1142755413,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777743933961,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scenario: You are managing a circular buffer for a printer that has 5 memory cells (Indices 1 to 5).\n\nInitial State:\n\nFRONT = 4, REAR = 5\n\nQUEUE Contents: The queue contains 'P', 'Q' at indices 4 and 5 respectively.\n\nArray Layout: [ _, _, _, P, Q ]\n\nTask: Describe the status of the FRONT, REAR, and the array contents after \n each of the following operations:\n\n        'R' and 'S' are added to the queue.\n        \n        One character is deleted from the queue.\n        \n        'T', 'U', and 'V' are added to the queue.\n        \n        Two characters are deleted from the queue.\n        \n        Check: Is the queue full or empty after step 4?",
      "fontSize": 15.787828640915267,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario: You are managing a circular buffer for a printer that has 5 memory cells (Indices 1 to 5).\n\nInitial State:\n\nFRONT = 4, REAR = 5\n\nQUEUE Contents: The queue contains 'P', 'Q' at indices 4 and 5 respectively.\n\nArray Layout: [ _, _, _, P, Q ]\n\nTask: Describe the status of the FRONT, REAR, and the array contents after \n each of the following operations:\n\n        'R' and 'S' are added to the queue.\n        \n        One character is deleted from the queue.\n        \n        'T', 'U', and 'V' are added to the queue.\n        \n        Two characters are deleted from the queue.\n        \n        Check: Is the queue full or empty after step 4?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jGuJHHYVVwArXHScMe8IT",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 218.98504404428536,
      "y": 7626.836479617112,
      "width": 771.2474365234375,
      "height": 580,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 662972603,
      "version": 4,
      "versionNonce": 598539931,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777743938996,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scenario: A Deque is implemented using a circular array of 6 memory cells (Indices 1 to 6).\n\nInitial State:\n\nThe Deque is currently empty.\n\nFRONT = -1, REAR = -1\n\nTask: Perform the following operations and track the FRONT and REAR pointers after each step:\n\ninsertRear('A')\n\ninsertRear('B')\n\ninsertFront('C')\n\ninsertFront('D')\n\ndeleteRear()\n\ninsertRear('E')\n\nQuestions to Answer:\n\nIdentify the final indices of FRONT and REAR.  \n\nList the elements currently in the Deque from FRONT to REAR.  \n\nExplain why insertFront on an empty Deque results in both pointers being the same.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario: A Deque is implemented using a circular array of 6 memory cells (Indices 1 to 6).\n\nInitial State:\n\nThe Deque is currently empty.\n\nFRONT = -1, REAR = -1\n\nTask: Perform the following operations and track the FRONT and REAR pointers after each step:\n\ninsertRear('A')\n\ninsertRear('B')\n\ninsertFront('C')\n\ninsertFront('D')\n\ndeleteRear()\n\ninsertRear('E')\n\nQuestions to Answer:\n\nIdentify the final indices of FRONT and REAR.  \n\nList the elements currently in the Deque from FRONT to REAR.  \n\nExplain why insertFront on an empty Deque results in both pointers being the same.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
